Sir, Barry Riley ('The long view', February 27/28) is of course correct when
he points out that British companies pay out too much dividend and retain
insufficient funds for reinvestment.
The chancellor can mitigate this situation at no cost to the Treasury by
increasing taxes on distributed profits and/or reducing taxes on profits
retained for reinvestment.
Christopher Haskins
chairman,
