Other officials said Unita had made several previous claims to complete
victory in Huambo, the main focus of renewed fighting between government and
Unita forces over the past two months.
The official news agency Angop carried an armed forces statement on Saturday
night which said intense fighting was continuing in the city of half a
million people.
But this was issued three hours before Vorgan, the rebel radio station, said
Unita forces controlled Huambo.
