<HEADLINE>
FT  06 MAR 93 / On the attack
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir Norman Fowler, Tory party chairman, yesterday demanded loyalty both to
the government's European policy and to Mr Major personally. He said party
unity could not be regarded as an 'optional extra' by Tory MPs
</TEXT>
<XX>
