<HEADLINE>
FT  06 MAR 93 / Finance and the Family: Britannia's guaranteed return - At a
Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Britannia Building Society has launched a new guaranteed account which has a
three year period, shorter than most other guaranteed products. However, the
method of calculating the investor's gain is quite different; rather than
the rise in the FT-SE 100 over the years, the investor's gain is 112.5 per
cent of the difference between the average of the FT-SE's level one, two and
three years hence, and the original level. So if FT-SE starts at 3,000 and
reaches 3,200, 3,400 and 3,600 in successive years, the gain will be around
15 per cent. The gain is net of basic rate tax; non-taxpayers can reclaim
the excess.
