<HEADLINE>
FT  06 MAR 93 / London Stock Exchange: Cookson rights
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOEL KIBAZO and STEVE THOMPSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Confirmation of a rights issue from industrial materials company Cookson
Group nevertheless surprised many market watchers and sent the shares into
retreat on an otherwise strong day in the market.
The company, which also announced figures in line with market expectations,
is to make a one-for-four rights issue at 170p a share to raise Pounds
185.6m to fund growth and reduce acquisitions. This is the second time
within the last two years that the company has called on the market for
cash.
The shares gave up 13 to 199p and Mr Andrew Mitchell at Smith New Court
said: 'The shares are unlikely to go anywhere until the potential disposals
and acquisitions are seen.'
</TEXT>
