<HEADLINE>
FT  06 MAR 93 / Early retirement pensions at Mirror
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
TRUSTEES of the Mirror Group Pension Fund yesterday announced the
reintroduction of early retirement arrangements for both active and deferred
pensioners. These were suspended after the discovery that more than Pounds
440m was missing from the pension schemes of companies controlled by the
late Robert Maxwell.
The arrangements will be available from the age of 56 to people who have
completed 25 years service. Those aged at least 60 will be allowed to
commute part of the pension for a lump sum.
Deferred pensioners who had at least 25 years service before they left the
company will have similar arrangements available to them, Mirror Group
Trustees said.
